      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "A good race. REWARDS AND MORE (6) led and deserved his win this grade and then was heavily bet again finding a couple better. He'll use the inside gate and back to a pet distance can make amends. COTEHELE (3) is a South Australian who has raced well in stronger than this. Resumes at Oakbank at Stakes level beaten 3.3L after settling a long way back. Proven second-up and Tourneur is here to ride. A winning chance if he takes to the circuit. DAKOTA LEE (2) has won 12/13 and 3/3 this course and distance. Flies fresh and draws low. Has the ability but 378 days off the scene is the niggle. The betting will be key. BOLDINHO (1) is down from Darwin and brings a string of wins. Maps well and Todd sticks. He'll be in the finish if presented on song. ZOURATA (5) was a bit plainer seeking the hat-trick over 1200m at Darwin, but he'd won there at this level by 8.3L prior. Has been freshened, and Tsaikos takes over from the apprentice. A player as well.",
